% no matter MOB level).   I don’t think any of these changes would make a wizard irreplacable, and clerics and chanters pretty much are already so spare me the spam about wanting to be Uber.  Useful is the goal (please see my post under Rants entitled “/feedback” for my views on class balance.<br>
<br>
 I’ll reserve judgment on this Teleportation direction until they implement their new “vision,” but I’d venture to say no one ever rolled up a wizard thinking “oh boy, isn’t it gonna be sweet when I can port people all over Norrath and the planes at will!”   This is pretty much akin to giving Mages weak pets (I know they are not but humor me) and then then Verant saying “we think there are two things mages do, summon pets and cast utility spells (coldstones, summoned weapons, etc.) .  We are going to beef up utility spells as we think this is where the class is headed.”  <br>
<br>
I think if druids never had ports, as should have been the case, maybe this ability would be something to get is in groups, but it isn’t the case so I’m afraid it’s pretty ho-hum.  Think about it, how many times have you heard the following: “Paying for TP to [Misty],[Lava],[Feerot]”?   Ever hear anyone say “Gee, can anyone TP me into the maze in Cazic?” Or when you do port someone, when they pop at the destination they immediately ask “do you know where the druid circle is from here?  I’m lost.”   Not to mention a “sow” either side of a port, and maybe a camo is always much appreciated.  We aren’t even close to druids at TP’ing.   IMHO Call of the Hero was so wizard, not mage, they should have named the spell “Screw Wizards.”<br>
<br>
So what would really define the wizard class IF all we had to work with was the teleportation concept?   Presuming we have seen the last of damage upgrades/refinement (I urge we have), I would like to see teleportation be made offensive rather than merely travel (ports) or defensive (evacs) only.    What do I mean?  OK, I haven’t thought this out yet, but something “like” any of the following:<br>
<br>
Set Teleport.  A wizard should be able to set one TP, much like an individual bind site, of their choice.  Make it subject to certain zone limitations (and yes, include the planes).  Make it expensive to cast (in mana, if not regents).  This would make us more useful in staging uber and planes-level battles.   Notice it’s not like CoH exactly, as the wizard needs to set the spot, return and port with the group members. <br>
<br>
Create Self Evac.  Have us able to imbue a single gem or item with a right-clickable personal evac.  Make it only function if the person is grouped with you (otherwise it’s just a money maker).  Make it no rent.    <br>
<br>
Teleport MOB#1.  Why not?   Don’t make it erase or reduce aggro, just TP one MOB far away in the same zone, enough to zone the party , get an evac or heal off.   Used with mez it eliminates an add you may never be ready for.<br>
<br>
Teleport MOB#2.  Set a TP point where you are fighting and be able to “port” a single, pissed off mob to the spot to fight it.   Make it visual/tight range castable only, but this would allow a wizard to scout a little ahead and be an effective puller in dense zones with high aggro radius.   <br>
<br>
General.  It also wouldn’t hurt to have us capable of setting multiple self bind affinities, have our evacs cast slightly faster than a druid’s (and/or more reliably), as being masters of something should mean you do it better. <br>
<br>
Note none of these are as imbalancing as returning a character to life with 90% experience or wiping aggro or speeding mana recovery.   None of these would make wizards irreplacable, but would make them wanted again maybe.   Any of these could be nerfed or worked with a bit to still render a useful class ability without destroying the mythical “balance.”    <br>
